name: Port strike update
summary: Concerns over the potential disruption caused by a port strike in the United States prompted government officials and industries to take proactive measures. The dockworkers' strike, aimed at addressing automation concerns and wage increases, raised fears of product shortages and price hikes. However, the situation has been resolved with dockworkers returning to work after reaching an agreement with employers, including a substantial 62% pay raise over six years. This agreement ended the East Coast strike, preventing further disruptions to the supply chain and averting a potential resurgence of toilet paper shortages.

summary: Kirk Cousins etched his name in Falcons history, setting a franchise record with 509 passing yards and throwing for four touchdowns. His exceptional performance led the Falcons to victory over the Buccaneers in an overtime thriller. Cousins joined an exclusive group of quarterbacks with 500-yard passing games, showcasing his exceptional talent. The Falcons' triumph was a testament to Cousins' heroics, which stunned NFL fans and further solidified his status as a rising star. His iconic "You Like That!" quote encapsulated the excitement and joy of the overtime win, cementing his place in Falcons lore.

name: Manchester United
summary: Manchester United endured a turbulent week, experiencing both triumph and adversity. In the Europa League, Harry Maguire played a pivotal role in rescuing his 10-man team, securing a thrilling 3-3 draw against Porto. However, their domestic woes continued as they suffered a humiliating 3-0 defeat at home to Tottenham Hotspur. Erik ten Hag's side failed to impress, prompting some fans to leave the stadium prematurely. Tottenham's convincing victory further deepened Manchester United's misery, with Bruno Fernandes receiving a red card and Spurs ruthlessly exploiting the numerical advantage.

name: Liz Cheney

Harris's decision to deploy Cheney is seen as an attempt to woo anti-Trump Republicans, while Cheney's appearance highlights her break from the Republican Party over its embrace of Trump. name: Matthew Perry
summary: A doctor has pleaded guilty in connection with the death of "Friends" star Matthew Perry. The doctor, who is charged with conspiracy to distribute ketamine, a powerful anesthetic, was involved in supplying the actor with the drug. Perry, who has struggled with substance abuse for many years, overdosed on ketamine in 2021. The guilty plea comes as part of a larger investigation into the illegal distribution of opioids and other drugs in California.
